**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:
The Watcher index action is not able to write to data streams due to using the op_type `index`, and not `create`. Watcher should be able to create documents in data streams.

**Steps to reproduce**:

 1. Create datasteam
 2. Create Watcher with index action 
 3. Execute Watcher

```json
PUT /_data_stream/logs-data-stream


PUT _watcher/watch/log_error_watch
{
  "trigger": {
    "schedule": {
      "interval": "100000h"
    }
  },
  "input": {
    "search": {
      "request": {
        "indices": [
          "logs"
        ],
        "body": {
          "query": {
            "match_all": {}
          }
        }
      }
    }
  },
  "actions": {
    "index_payload": {
      "index": {
        "index": "logs-data-stream",
        "doc_id": "my-id"
      }
    }
  }
}

POST _watcher/watch/log_error_watch/_execute

DELETE _watcher/watch/log_error_watch

DELETE _data_stream/logs-data-stream
```

