**Description of the problem including expected versus actual behavior**:
EQL queries with "sequence by" statements fail to execute with an error when any of the documents in a sequence contain an array value in the aggregation field.

**Elasticsearch version** (`bin/elasticsearch --version`):
```js
  "version" : {
    "number" : "8.0.0-SNAPSHOT",
    "build_flavor" : "default",
    "build_type" : "deb",
    "build_hash" : "8f8d2d1b4ba31c6da040598a91e9aa559e093a4a",
  }
```

**Steps to reproduce**:
 1. Index two documents. The first document should have a single value for `host.name`. The second document should have an array of values for `host.name`:
```js
PUT /test-index-1/_doc/1
{
  "@timestamp": "2020-11-03T08:51:55.337Z",
  "host": {
    "name": "testhost"
  }
}

PUT /test-index-1/_doc/2
{
  "@timestamp": "2020-11-03T08:51:56.337Z",
  "host": {
    "name": ["testhost", "foo"]
  }
}
```
 2. Run an EQL sequence query with a `by` statement like so:
```js
GET /test-index-1/_eql/search
{
  "query": """
    sequence by host.name with maxspan=15m
    [any where true]
    [any where true]
  """
}
```
 3. Observe that the following error is returned:
```js
{
  "error" : {
    "root_cause" : [
      {
        "type" : "ql_illegal_argument_exception",
        "reason" : "Arrays (returned by [host.name]) are not supported"
      }
    ],
    "type" : "ql_illegal_argument_exception",
    "reason" : "Arrays (returned by [host.name]) are not supported"
  },
  "status" : 500
}
```

When a `search_as_you_type` field is nested under an object, then `exists` queries on the object field will fail:

```yml
PUT test
{
    "mappings": {
        "properties": {
            "object": {
                "properties": {
                    "field": {
                        "type": "search_as_you_type"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

POST test/_doc
{
  "object.field": "value"
}

POST test/_search?q=object:*
```

Error:
```
java.lang.UnsupportedOperationException
org.elasticsearch.index.mapper.SearchAsYouTypeFieldMapper$PrefixFieldType.existsQuery(SearchAsYouTypeFieldMapper.java:397)
org.elasticsearch.index.query.ExistsQueryBuilder.newObjectFieldExistsQuery(ExistsQueryBuilder.java:214)
org.elasticsearch.index.query.ExistsQueryBuilder.newFieldExistsQuery(ExistsQueryBuilder.java:202)
org.elasticsearch.index.query.ExistsQueryBuilder.newFilter(ExistsQueryBuilder.java:164)
org.elasticsearch.index.search.QueryStringQueryParser.existsQuery(QueryStringQueryParser.java:635)
```

